net.sf.mmm.search.view.api

Interface SearchEntryTypeView

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AttributeReadId<String>, AttributeReadTitle<String>, SearchEntryType
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SearchEntryTypeViewBean

    public interface SearchEntryTypeView
extends SearchEntryType
    This interface represents the view on a SearchEntryType.
    If you configure multiple SearchEntryTypes with the same title these are combined to one SearchEntryTypeView. The first of these that has an icon set is used to define the ID and icon of this SearchEntryTypeView. Further only the SearchEntryTypes are represented for which there are actually SearchEntrys in the index.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
